text: Fidalgo is an unincorporated community in Skagit County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Fidalgo was established in 1870, and remained in operation until 1910. The community takes its name from nearby Fidalgo Bay. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Skagit County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Fidalgo, Washington
